HEADWORD: Portly
<hw>Port"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Port</er>
demeanor.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a dignified port or mien; of a
noble appearance; imposing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Bulky; corpulent.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>portly</xex>
personage.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dickens.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portman</ent>⟦br⟧
